quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  40,38,"and he who believed said, 'O my people! follow me, I will guide you to the way of the right direction"
  40,39,"O my people! verily, the life of this world is but a provision, but, verily, the hereafter, that is the abode of stability"
  40,40,"Whoso does evil, he shall only be recompensed with the like thereof , and whoso does right, be it male or female and a believer, these shall enter into Paradise; they shall be provided therein without count"
  40,41,"O my people! why should I call you to salvation, and you call me to the fire"
  40,42,"Ye call on me to disbelieve in God, and to join with Him what I have no knowledge of; but I call you to the mighty forgiving One"
  40,43,"no doubt that what ye call me to, ought not to be called on in this world or in the hereafter, and that we shall be sent back to God, and that the extravagant, they are the fellows of the Fire"
  40,44,"But ye shall remember what I say to you; and I entrust my affair to God, verily, God looks upon His servants"
  40,45,"And God guarded him from the evils of what they plotted, and there closed in upon Pharaoh evil woe"
  40,46,"The fire - they shall be exposed to it morning and evening; and 'on the day the Hour shall arise,' enter, O people of Pharaoh! into the keenest torment"
  40,47,"And when they argue together in the fire, and the weak say to those who were big with pride, 'Verily, we were followers of yours, can ye then avail us against a portion of the fire"
  40,48,"Those who were big with pride shall say, 'Verily, we are all in it; verily, God has judged between His servants"
  40,49,"And those who are in the fire shall say unto the keepers of hell, 'Call upon your Lord to lighten from us one day of the torment"
  40,50,"They shall say, 'Did not your apostles come to you with manifest signs?' They shall say, 'Yea!' They shall say, 'Then call!- but the call of the misbelievers is only in error"